        <body>       
                
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>1828 RITTENHOUSE SQUARE.<lb/>
                April 6<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 87<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear M<hi rend="sup">r</hi>. Morais<lb/></p>
            <p>Mother asks<lb/> me to write for her as her<lb/> eyes are not yet quite<lb/> strong.  M<hi rend="sup">rs</hi>. John<lb/> Edgar Thomson called up&#45;<lb/>on her today in regard<lb/> to a Russian&#45;Jewish boy&#44;<lb/> twelve years old&#44; William<lb/> Abrahamson by name.<lb/>  He came out here as a<lb/> stow&#45;away&#44; and being<lb/> sick&#44; was put in the<lb/> Children&#39;s Hospital<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>22<hi rend="sup">nd</hi> St just below<lb/> Walnut&#44; opposite St<lb/> James Place&#44; a<lb/> hospital in which M<hi rend="sup">rs</hi>.<lb/> Thomson has always<lb/> taken great interest.<lb/>  She has been troubled<lb/> about the child because<lb/> he is so conscientious<lb/> that he will not eat<lb/> the food prepared in<lb/> the institution.  Mother<lb/> went to see him this<lb/> afternoon&#44; found him<lb/> very bright&#44; but of<lb/> course he ought to<lb/> have strenthening<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>food.  He has letters<lb/> from his mother in<lb/> Liverpool&#44; Eng. written<lb/> in Hebrew&#44; &#38; he seems<lb/> anxious to go home to<lb/> her for his <hi rend="underline">Barmitzva</hi><lb/> next year.  Mother<lb/> would be very glad if<lb/> you could visit him&#44;<lb/> &#38; suggest anything else<lb/> to her to be done in the case.<lb/>  She has promised to<lb/> send him some <hi rend="underline">matsos</hi>.<lb/>  I believe he went to the<lb/> United Hebrew Charities<lb/> before entering the<lb/> Hospital&#44; but they did<lb/> not do anything for<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="4"/>
            <p>him.<lb/></p>
            <p>With regards to<lb/> all with you&#44; from<lb/> Mother and self<lb/> Sincerely<lb/> Mary M. Cohen<lb/></p>
                
            <p>Mother asks me to add<lb/> that <hi rend="underline">if possible</hi>&#44; she hopes<lb/> that you will see the boy <hi rend="underline">before</hi><lb/> Passover&#44; &#38; let her know<lb/> if you think there is anything<lb/> else she could do for<lb/> him.<lb/></p>
            </body>
